Install AndroidStudio: https://developer.android.com/studio

Launch an Android simulator Pixel 9 Pro API 36.0

Install Maestro https://maestro.dev/:

To install the CLI, first ensure Java 17 or higher is installed and JAVA_HOME points to it. Then run:
curl -fsSL "https://get.maestro.mobile.dev" | bash

To run the test via CLI:
cd into the directory DemoShop
Run: maestro test --include-tags=regression .

You can also install Maestro Studio and run it directly from there.
You can either run individual test by opening the yaml file or you can set the environment (top right corner)
and add <regression> to "includeTags" "Run All Tests" will not only run tests tagged with regression.
